comments.body:
No need to re-acquire `cs_wallet` here (`RecursiveUpdateTxState` already locks `cs_wallet`) . Can add the exclusive lock annotation instead, e.g:

```c++
const auto& try_update_state = [&](CWalletTx& wtx) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(cs_wallet) {
    if (conflictconfirms >= GetTxDepthInMainChain(wtx)) return false;
    
    wtx.m_state = TxStateConflicted{hashBlock, conflicting_height};
    return true;
};
```

(same for the others)

